LinkSmart Supernode 2.2.0-SNAPSHOT
------------------------------------------------------------

Requirements
------------
Java 1.7
JCE unlimited strength


Starting and Stopping LinkSmart
------------------------------------------------------------

To start the LinkSmart supernode , run the following command in Windows:

bin\karaf.bat

respectively on Unix:

bin/karaf

upon successful startup, a welcome message would appear. 

Please wait for a while (10-15 seconds) so that LinkSmart components are installed and activated by the container.

you can view the the log from LinkSmart Supernode components:
karaf@root()> log:display
or
karaf@root()> log:tail

to see the (OSGi) bundles status:
karaf@root()> bundle:list


To stop the supernode from the console, enter ^D in the console:

^D

Alternatively, you can also run the following command:

system:shutdown

or simply

shutdown -f

